<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="168" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,501,476,502]" box="[151,501,476,502]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,501,476,502]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,501,476,502]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Selys, 1853" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1853" box="[238,501,476,502]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Dysphaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,357,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Dysphaea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Selys" box="[364,501,476,502]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" refString="Selys Longchamps, E. de (1853) Synopsis des Calopterygines. Bulletins de l'Academie Royale des sciences, des lettres et des beaux-arts de Belgique, 20, 1 - 73." type="journal article" year="1853">Selys, 1853</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,546,751]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
Members of this genus have a largely black and robust body in males and females. Wings almost as long as abdomen and are parallel sided and often distinctly colored in the males. Male anal appendages are black, cerci are twice as long as S10, separated widely at base and hollowed out interiorly in the apical half. Their apices are curved and positioned close or overlapping. The left and right tips of male genital ligula curl greatly. Species of this genus are found at large open streams and rivers. In Vietnam, three species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1853" box="[1033,1145,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Dysphaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1033,1145,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Dysphaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded: 
<taxonomicName authority="Martin, 1904" authorityName=": Martin" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Dysphaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basitincta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">D. basitincta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martin" box="[268,417,726,751]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" refString="Martin, R. (1904) Liste des Nevropteres de l'Indo-Chine. In: Auguste, P. (Aut.), Mission Pavie Indo-Chine 1879 - 1895. Etudes diverses. III. Recherches sur l'histoire naturelle de l'Indo-Chine orientale. Ernest Leroux, Paris, pp. 204 - 221." type="book chapter" year="1904">Martin, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hamalainen, 2012" authorityName=": Hamalainen" authorityYear="2012" box="[428,776,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Dysphaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haomiao">
<emphasis box="[428,561,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">D. haomiao</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hamalainen" box="[568,776,726,751]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" refString="Hamalainen, M. (2012) Dysphaea haomiao sp. nov. from China and Vietnam (Odonata: Euphaeidae). International Journal of Odonatology, 14, 305 - 311. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 13887890.2011.638618" type="journal article" year="2012">Hämäläinen, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser, 1938" authorityName=": Fraser" authorityYear="1938" box="[834,1111,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Euphaeidae" genus="Dysphaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosa">
<emphasis box="[834,961,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">D. gloriosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fraser" box="[969,1111,727,751]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" refString="Fraser, F. C. (1938) Two new species of Oriental Odonata. Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society, London, 7 (B), 197 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1938. tb 01228. x" type="journal article" year="1938">Fraser, 1938</bibRefCitation>
